description: Prevent business logic from leaking into Next.js API routes
globs: "**/src/app/api/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Next.js API Routes

Business logic and external callbacks (webhooks, payment flows, notifications) live in **Convex** — not in Next.js API routes.

- Do not create files under `src/app/api/`. Convex HTTP actions (`convex/http.ts`) handle all webhook endpoints.
- If a Next.js server component needs data, use Convex queries via the client, not a local API route.
- The only exception is Next.js middleware for redirects or auth guards, which is fine in `middleware.ts`.
